==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Graphotype
<hw>Graph"o*type</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>gra`fein</grk> to write + <ets>-type</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Engraving)</fld> <def>A process for producing a design upon a
surface in relief so that it can be printed from. Prepared chalk or
oxide of zinc is pressed upon a smooth plate by a hydraulic press, and
the design is drawn upon this in a peculiar ink which hardens the
surface wherever it is applied. The surface is then carefully rubbed or
brushed, leaving the lines in relief.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>-graphy</ent>⟦br⟧
